                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.857Ar1/21</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Cork</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FW1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Frost</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Queenstown</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1915-08-22T09:00:00-05:00"
                            notBefore="1915-08-21T00:00:00-00:25">
                            <hi rend="italic">undated</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received August 22, 1915, 9 a.
                        m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Have failed in devoutest efforts to discover any evidence that <hi rend="italic"
                        >Arabic</hi> was warned by submarine or convoyed by war vessel. She did not
                    attempt to ram submarine nor go to assistance of <hi rend="italic">Dunsley</hi>.
                    It is barely possible, however, that other facts may yet be found.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Frost</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
